    <p>
      Scarab uses a database acess layer based on <a href="http://db.apache.org/torque">Torque</a>.
      So it should be able to run on any of the databases supported by Torque.
      We don't have the resources to perform full testing with all RDBM-systems and
      we need help from the community to verify it works fine.
    </p>

    <p>
     The table above lists all databases, known to have worked with
     Scarab-releases from our users' experience. 

     Databases marked as "<font color="green"><b>Fully&#160;supported</b></font>" 
     are verified to work with the current release and the integration 
     documentation has been verified.

     Databases marked as "<font color="orange"><b>Partial&#160;supported</b></font>" 
     have been tested with the current release, but either the integration 
     is complex, or not well documented. Help from the comunity is needed.
     
     Databases marked as "<font color="red"><b>Not&#160;supported</b></font>" 
     have not been tested with the current release. Help from the comunity
     is needed.
    </p>

    <p> 
      If you need any help, ask for it in the 
      <a href="http://scarab.tigris.org/servlets/ProjectMailingListList">mailing lists</a>.
      We will try to get it working!
    </p>


